quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  67,15,"He is the One who made the earth tame for you, so walk in its tracts and eat of His provision. The resurrection is to Him"
  67,16,Are you safe from the One in the sky that He does not make you sink in the earth when it suddenly shakes
  67,17,Or are you safe from the One in the sky that He does not send a sandstorm upon you? Then you are going to know how My warning is
  67,18,"And those before them have certainly denied, so how was My rejection (and punishment)"
  67,19,Or did they not look at the birds above them spreading (their) wings and folding them? What holds them except the beneficent? He sees everything
  67,20,"Or who is this, the one who is an army for you helping you, other than the beneficent? The disbelievers are only in deception"
  67,21,"Or who is this, the one who provides for you if He withholds His provision? No, but they insist on rebellion and hatred"
  67,22,Is someone who walks with his face downward better guided or someone who walks properly on a straight path
  67,23,"Say: He is the One who created you and made the hearing and the sight and the heart for you, but you thank a little"
  67,24,"say: He is the One who scattered you on the earth, and you will be gathered to Him"
  67,25,"And they say: when is this promise, if you are truthful"
  67,26,"Say: the knowledge of it is only with God, and I am only to warn clearly"
  67,27,"Then when they see it near, faces of those who disbelieved turns gloomy, and it is said: this is that which you used to called for"
  67,28,"Say: what do you think if God destroys me and those with me or He has mercy on us, then who protects the disbelievers from a painful punishment"
  67,29,"Say: He is the beneficent, we believed in Him and we trust in Him, and you are going to know who is in an obvious error"
  67,30,"Say: what do you think if your water (sinks deep and) becomes dried up, then who brings you (fresh) running water"